observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management:

make representation with the LBP and request a detailed information on the transacted online fund transfers made through the LBP weAccess banking facility;


immediately submit the complete documents supporting the fund transfers to enable the Audit Team to conduct the proper review and evaluation;

submit the Acknowledgment Screen/Transaction Acknowledgement Receipt of the fund transfer transactions since it was emailed to the registered email/s address/es of the maker/s and authorizer/s of the LGU to the Auditor’s Office and prove the regularity and legality of these transactions through attachment of pertinent documentary requirements as indicated in COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012 and COA Circular 2023-004 dated June 14, 2023; and

ensure that the financial transactions were properly recorded and reported in the book of accounts of the Municipality in compliance with related rules and regulations.

We recommended that Management:
make representation with LANBANK and request a detailed information on the transacted online fund transfers made through the LANDBANK weAccess banking facility;
immediately submit the complete documents supporting the fund transfers to enable the Audit Team to conduct the proper review and evaluation;
submit the Acknowledgment Screen/Transaction Acknowledgement Receipt of the fund transfer transactions since it was emailed to the registered email/s address/es of the maker/s and authorizer/s of the LGU to the Auditor’s Office and prove the regularity and legality of these transactions through attachment of pertinent documentary requirements as indicated in COA Circular 2012-001 dated June 14, 2012 and COA Circular 2023-004 dated June 14, 2023; and
ensure that the financial transactions were properly recorded and reported in the book of accounts of the Municipality in compliance with related rules and regulations.
Management Comment/s: The Management commented that it is currently securing a copy of the documents from the bank and is in the process of submitting the complete DVs supporting the fund transfers.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive adopt strategic courses of action and instruct the following:

The Finance Committee to strive to improve their cash management with a view of meeting the Municipality’s obligation as they become due;

The Budget Office to re-assess their budget planning to execution processes to ascertain and pinpoint the cause/s of incurrence of cash deficit and to work out and aggressively pursue feasible solutions that can address the issue involving the fiscal operation of the Municipality;

The Local Finance Committee to carefully determine the projected revenues and income that can be reasonably collected in line with its mandate to generate adequate revenue and income for the Municipality;

The Municipal Treasurer to intensify tax campaign activity and issue notices or demand letters to delinquent real property taxpayers for the settlement of unpaid local taxes; and

The Business Licensing and Permit Office (BPLO) to monitor and enforce necessary revenue measures to all business enterprises on the payment of permits and licenses in order to attain the projected revenues of the Municipality.

